#!CNavyBlue 
#!N  #!Ruseimag Using the Image Window #!N #!EC #!N #!N Once 
an image appears in the Image window, it can be altered 
and manipulated in many ways. This section describes how to manipulate 
the image directly, using the interactor features accessed through the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Options #!EF menu in the Image window. #!N #!N #!I0 #!N 
Notes: #!N #!I30 #!N 1. These features are enabled  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   only 
#!EF if you used the Image tool in your visual program 
to render the image. If you used another tool, such as 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Display #!EF , you will not be able to use 
many of the Image window options. The Image tool is found 
in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Rendering #!EF category. See  #!Limage,dxall860 h Image  #!EL  in IBM Visualization 
Data Explorer User's Reference for more information. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. 
It is also possible to control many characteristics of the Image 
widow by using input parameters to the Image tool. These parameters 
are hidden by default but can be accessed with the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Expose #!EF button in the Image tool's Configuration dialog box (which 
itself is accessed by selecting the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Configuration #!EF option in 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF pull-down menu of the Visual Program Editor) For 
more information, see Image in the IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's 
Reference. #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF 
